"Are you the walking 500,000?"
Tongbai Police released a video, searching for 500,000 people through street skits and secret codes, and said: "Spies are around us, they may be passers-by who pass by you"
"Let us open our eyes together and look for the 500,000 people walking around us"

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: According to research, this behavior of "catching spies through skit codes" is not a joke, but a way of "catching spies" recognized by the People's Daily and many police media. It originated during the Hong Kong protests in 2019, when a Weibo netizen expressed the hope that young people on both sides could bridge the gap and understand each other. One person replied "Palace Jade Wine?" (a famous line from a Spring Festival Gala skit) However, the netizen said that he was older and did not understand the other party's meaning, so he was considered a spy and was forwarded by many police media and the People's Daily. Since then, "skit codes" have become a way to catch spies.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On August 3, a very unique basketball game took place. In the National Youth U17 Women's Basketball Final, the Shandong team won the runner-up despite a 33-point victory over their opponents. The reason is that according to the competition rules, the ranking of the game is based on a comprehensive assessment of multiple indicators such as game scores, quality, technical standards, and technical evaluation. Therefore, the Shandong team, which was relatively low in physical tests and technical evaluations, could only be the runner-up.
